definition.value: The conjugate base of an N-choloyl-L-alpha-amino acid.
A pentadecenoic acid having its double bond in the 9-position.
A 9-pentadecenoic acid in which the double bond adopts cis-configuration.
A 9-pentadecenoic acid in which the double bond adopts trans-configuration.

A N-hydroxysuccinimide ester resulting from the formal condensation of the two carboxy groups of suberic acid with the hydroxy group of 1-hydroxypyrrolidine-2,5-dione. It is a noncleavable and membrane permeable crosslinker.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is adenosine 5'-monophosphate in which one of the hydroxy groups of the phosphate has been condensed with the carboxylic acid group of L-arginine.
A sterol 3-beta-D-glucoside having solasodine as the sterol component.
A nitrosothio compound that is coenzyme A in which the thiol group is replaced by a nitrososulfanediyl group.

A pyrazolopyridine that is 1H-pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyridine substituted by 1H-pyrazol-3-yl, (3-endo)-3-hydroxy-8-oxabicyclo[3.2.1]octan-3-yl, and (3R)-3-methylmorpholin-4-yl groups at positions 1, 4 and 6, respectively. It is a highly potent and selective inhibitor of ATR kinase (IC50 = 1 nM).
An hydroxysulfenamide glutathione peptide anion; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An epoxide that is cyclohexene substituted at positions 3 and 4 by an epoxy group.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 3,4-dimethoxy-L-phenylalanine; major species at pH 7.3.
A cinnamate that is the conjugate base of 3,4-dimethoxycinnamic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A secondary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of herquline C resulting from the protonation of the secondary amino group; Major species at pH 7.3.
A L-tyrosine derivative that is L-dopa in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4 of the phenyl ring are replaced by methoxy groups.

An aryl sulfide that is benzene substituted by {[2-(methoxycarbonyl)phenyl]methyl}amino, fluoro, chloro, and (2,2,2-trifluoroethyl)sulfanediyl groups at positions 1, 2, 4 and 5, respectively. It is an acaricide discovered by Shandong Kangqiao Bio-technology Co. Ltd that is highly effective against citrus rust mites, red spider mites, and two-spotted spider mites and has excellent leaf penetration properties.

A member of the class of 1,3-thiazoles that is 1,3-thiazole substituted by pyridin-3-yl, chloro, and ethyl[3-(methylsulfonyl)propanoyl]amino groups at positions 2, 4 and 5, respectively. It is an insecticide developed by Corteva that has excellent activity against sap-feeding insects.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

Any sesquiterpenoid with a cadinane skeleton.
Major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methyl-1H-pyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 2-[2,4-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy]aniline. It is a fungicide developed by Shandong United Pesticide Industry Co. that demonstrates effective control against soybean rust, corn rust, and wheat powdery mildew.
